                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Wizzies have shackles...
<br />

<br />
Necromancers have their dot-snares...
<br />

<br />
Mages...don`t need it =P
<br />

<br />
And Enchanters....Need it?
<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"> PROS </span>
<br />
It would help (and encourage) charming for the lower levels who dont have the advantages such as Arcane Rune.
<br />

<br />
It would increase the demand for Enchanters
<br />

<br />
If a mob is coming after you and you arent runed you have time to root/mezz it w/o having to pray that you channel the spell.
<br />

<br />
And others...
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold"> CONS </span>
<br />
On top of what we already have to do, it would just be annoying for the tank or annoying bard to say, 'Chanter, wake up! Snare this mob!'
<br />

<br />
It could potentially be harsh on the mana
<br />

<br />
Adding a sixth class, (RNG, DRU, NEC, SHD, WIZ currently) to the snarer classes isn`t really BALENCING classes its just making all the classes the same in theory.
<br />

<br />
What do you think? Please vote and cast your reply!
<br />

<br />
I KNOW it seems far fetched but i didnt see a poll about it and id be interested  =D> 
<br />
Laeiin the Forgotten</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
