                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We used to have a ghetto type snare with our debuffs then hand the mob a weap but that was nerfed. 
<br />

<br />
At the time I beleive the reasoning was class purity or something.  Since then we've seen druids get the mask of the hunter line of spells and other mana regen stuff.
<br />

<br />
Druids also received the CH line of spells although not as large as clerics still very usefull.
<br />

<br />
Then to add to that they have instant evacs etc.
<br />

<br />
Add to that the ability they have to charm mobs (which is not cha based it seems) and their ability to snare and you have a very powerfull charm class.  
<br />

<br />
Although limited by mob choice (animals only) it not too difficult to use your track to find the mob you require to get the job done.
<br />

<br />
Then theirs the necros ablility to snare (although not as long as a druids)  and then charm an undead mob you have a powerfull charm class as well.
<br />

<br />
The necro can also heal its  pet, DS its pet (as we can chanters but no where near a druids ability) and of course mez the pet if it breaks its charm.
<br />

<br />
All else failing of course they have the nice distinction of feign death , invul buff and and inate ability to heal themselves with taps etc.
<br />

<br />
Chanters have  the capacity to slow the mobs (which is very nice) mez the mobs on break and , um mem blur I guess.
<br />

<br />
We cannot heal our pet as such, cannot evac save the use of gate, heal ourselves,  save the use of runes which are more preventative than cure, or fegn death to remove ourselves from danger.
<br />
Dont get me wrong,  I have played all 3 class's and know their strengths and weakness's however I seem to have missed the class purity part somewhere that SOE use to resolve many role based issues.
<br />

<br />
I personally would love to see our weakness spell revamped to the times this many years on and encumber our mobs.  
<br />

<br />
I would then beleive we would be on par with the other charm class's.  Sure we can charm anything charmable however the diversity of charm control and recovery is definitaly not in the chanter class.
<br />

<br />
The funny thing is,  with such HIGH risk involved in the charming process we still suffer a very harsh charm penalty. 
<br />

<br />
End resolve.  I partner with a druid and own everything <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
